The EFF will appeal the interdict granted to Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan JOHANNESBURG - The EFF will appeal the interdict granted to Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan. He applied for an urgent interdict last Tuesday to suspend remedial action in the Public Protector's report on the so-called SARS rogue unit. The North Gauteng High Court earlier granted a suspension, pending the finalisation of a review of the report. WATCH: Court suspends PP's remedial actions against Gordhan Meanwhile, the Public Protector's office isn't happy with the ruling. Spokesperson Oupa Segwale said they are disappointed that the court found the functions of the NPA, police and State Security Minister can be suspended. "We will go back and study judgment and map the way forward," said Segwale.